comments: Prince (BKN) deflects the pass away from Covington (MIN).
Dinwiddie (BKN) legally contests Culver's (MIN) jump shot attempt.
Prince (BKN) makes contact with Culver's (MIN) arm and affects his driving shot attempt.
Jordan (BKN) establishes his position in Napier's (MIN) path while setting the screen and does not deliver contact.
Jordan (BKN) sets the screen on Culver (MIN) and does not deliver contact.
Culver (MIN) initiates contact with Dinwiddie (BKN) that affects his trajectory during the driving shot attempt.
Jordan (BKN) jumps and makes contact with Dieng's (MIN) left arm that affects his driving shot attempt.
Jordan (BKN) sets the screen on Napier (MIN) and does not deliver contact.
Jordan (BKN) extends his arm into Napier's (MIN) back and dislodges him from his defensive position.
Covington (MIN) maintains a legal guarding position on Prince (BKN) during the drive.
Dinwiddie (BKN) makes incidental contact with Covington (MIN) as the players pass each other.
Prince (BKN) has two hands briefly rested on Covington (MIN) before releasing as Covington moves to set the screen.
Dieng (MIN) sets the screen on Dinwiddie (BKN) and does not deliver contact.
Dieng (MIN) and Dinwiddie (BKN) briefly engage and separate during the rebound.
The ball is loose when Brooklyn requests a time out. Since neither team had possession at the time, a timeout should not have been awarded.
Jordan (BKN) makes marginal contact with Martin (MIN) while going for the tip.

During the throw-in, Bell (MIN) goes through the cylinder and strikes the basketball after it hits the rim, which is a violation on the throw-in. A substitute throw-in should have been awarded to Brooklyn and the game clock reset at 00:00.2.
